```text
All comparisons were performed under a fixed dual-ledger evaluation protocol. The first ledger held out aberration realizations while preserving the object-family distribution, whereas the second ledger held out entire object families that were not used during training. For each method, we used the same random seeds, object splits, aberration parameters, preprocessing steps, and aggregation pipeline. Confidence intervals were computed across independent seeds using bootstrap resampling unless otherwise stated. No samples were removed after evaluation, and all raw per-seed results are included in the source-data package.
```

